"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518386","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-12","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) is continuing to tighten rules on personal service companies and off-payroll workers. For example, it has successfully used Managed Service Company legislation to tackle tax avoidance involving personal service companies and intends to pursue people behind the schemes for tax debts.</p><p> </p><p>The 2016 Budget announced changes to improve the effectiveness of the intermediaries rules in the public sector. HMRC is also developing, with stakeholders, a new online tool for the public and private sectors to provide greater certainty about the tax rules.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-05-12T09:35:11.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518386/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518386/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518386/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-10","Tax Avoidance: Private Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he plans to take to ensure that private sector companies are responsible for their off-payroll workers who use personal service companies paying the correct amount of tax.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","36952"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518387","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-12","<p>The new Lifetime ISA will provide savers with the flexibility to save towards a first home and retirement at the same time.</p><p> </p><p>From April 2017, people aged 18 to 40 will be able to save up to £4,000 each year into a Lifetime ISA and receive a 25% bonus from the Government.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is engaging with the industry on the detail of implementation, regulation and advice on the Lifetime ISA. Further details will be announced when the Government brings forward legislation to enact the Lifetime ISA in the autumn.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","36954","2016-05-12T07:26:10.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518387/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518387/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518387/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-10","Individual Savings Accounts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when Lifetime ISAs will be available to the public.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","36953"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518388","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-12","<p>The new Lifetime ISA will provide savers with the flexibility to save towards a first home and retirement at the same time.</p><p> </p><p>From April 2017, people aged 18 to 40 will be able to save up to £4,000 each year into a Lifetime ISA and receive a 25% bonus from the Government.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is engaging with the industry on the detail of implementation, regulation and advice on the Lifetime ISA. Further details will be announced when the Government brings forward legislation to enact the Lifetime ISA in the autumn.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","36953","2016-05-12T07:26:10.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518388/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518388/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518388/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-10","Individual Savings Accounts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he plans to take to offer public financial advice on Lifetime ISAs.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","36954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518389","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-12","<p>Within HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) debt management teams in Worthing and Edinburgh are responsible for initiating insolvency actions where other attempts to recover sums due have been unsuccessful. A third team at Newcastle lodges HMRC’s claims in insolvencies. The total number of staff engaged on insolvency work in HMRC’s debt management offices is 258.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-12T10:37:35.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518389/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518389/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518389/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-10","Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many staff at HM Revenue and Customs work on insolvency procedures.","false","Biography information for Nigel Mills","Amber Valley","Nigel Mills","37006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518390","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-12","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) only holds information about dividends paid for each of the last two years. In 2014/15 a total of £70.6m was received. In 2015/16 the figure was £74.5m. These figures represent dividends paid after a company or individual has been made insolvent. HMRC also receives payments in response to the initiation of insolvency proceedings and these payments are sometimes sufficient to allow HMRC to withdraw the proceedings. Data is not available about the amount received by way of these payments.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-12T10:38:22.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518390/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518390/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518390/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-10","Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much HM Revenue and Customs has received related to insolvency procedures in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Nigel Mills","Amber Valley","Nigel Mills","37007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518391","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-12","<p>The new Lifetime ISA is an additional flexible savings product which will complement pensions to give savers greater freedom and choice to save for the long-term in a way that works for them.</p><p> </p><p>With automatic enrolment already helping nine million people with their pensions, the Government remains committed to supporting people who save in different ways.</p><p> </p><p>Increasing the choice of savings products available, the Lifetime ISA supports the Government’s ambition to encourage a regular savings habit amongst young people and to create a culture of long-term saving by offering the right products to suit their changing circumstances at different points in their lives.</p><p> </p><p>From April 2017, people aged 18 to 40 will be able to save up to £4,000 each year into a Lifetime ISA and receive a 25% bonus from the Government. Under the new Lifetime ISA, young savers will no longer have to choose between saving for their first home purchase or for retirement.</p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-05-12T09:26:01.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518391/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518391/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518391/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-10","Individual Savings Accounts: Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether it is his Department's policy that employees should be offered the choice of either auto-enrolment or paying into a Lifetime ISA as a means for saving for their pension, or that employees who wish to invest in a Lifetime ISA must do so in addition to auto-enrolment.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","37003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518392","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-12","<p>The amount spent by HM Revenue and Customs’ (HMRC) debt management offices in Worthing, Edinburgh and Newcastle on staff costs and insolvency expenses (e.g. court fees and payments to insolvency practitioners) was £32,594,200 in 2012/13, £26,337,346 in 2013/14, £30,295,668 in 2014/15 and £28,171,282 in 2015/16. Full data is not available for 2011/12. Across HMRC there are other staff working on specialist areas of insolvency but in the time available we cannot provide details of numbers or cost.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-12T10:35:39.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518392/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518392/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518392/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-10","Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the cost was to HM Revenue and Customs related to insolvency procedures in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Nigel Mills","Amber Valley","Nigel Mills","37008"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518393","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-12","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) is a creditor of anyone who has a tax debt. We do not have complete information about the number of debtors who have owed money to HMRC in the past five years.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-12T10:36:43.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518393/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518393/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518393/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-10","Revenue and Customs: Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many times HM Revenue and Customs has been a creditor in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Nigel Mills","Amber Valley","Nigel Mills","37009"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518394","Department for Education","false","2016-05-12","<p>In 2014-15 the spend on Special Educational Needs support for children under five years from the high needs block of the dedicated schools grant allocated to Lancashire County Council was about £2.53 million. This information is as reported by the local authority and published in the following document: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/section-251-outturn-2014-to-2015-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/section-251-outturn-2014-to-2015-data</a></p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-05-12T09:19:05.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518394/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518394/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518394/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-10","Special Educational Needs: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much of the Dedicated Schools Grant allocated to Lancashire County Council was spent on Special Educational Needs support for children under five years old in the last year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","37002"
