"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518144","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-05-12","<p>Replacing maintenance grants with loans for new full-time students in 2016/17 will ensure the higher education system remains financially sustainable whilst enabling the sector to make progress in widening participation amongst those from disadvantaged backgrounds. The Government will continue to monitor and evaluate a wide range of data and evidence relating to the Higher Education sector. This will include data on application and participation rates from the Universities and Colleges Admissions Service (UCAS) and the Higher Education Statistics Agency (HESA), as well as take-up and repayment rates of student financial support using Student Loans Company (SLC) data.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-05-12T09:51:59.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518144/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518144/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518144/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-05-09","Students: Grants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what measures the Government has (a) planned and (b) implemented to monitor the effects of abolishing student maintenance grants on students that the equality impact analysis identified would be disproportionately affected by that policy.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","36932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518145","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-05-12","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The November 2015 Higher Education Green Paper <em>(Teaching Excellence, Social Mobility and Student Choice)</em> confirms the Government’s intention to introduce, for the first time, a new system of alternative student finance. Subject to Parliament, the Government plans to introduce the system through new primary legislation.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-05-12T09:58:47.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518145/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518145/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/518145/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-05-09","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, from which academic year the Government plans that a Sharia-compliant student loan will be available for Muslim students.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","36933"
