"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517861","Department for International Development","false","2016-05-11","<p>The table below shows the amount of Official Development Assistance (ODA) spent on education in Bangladesh by the United Kingdom through the government, NGOs and civil society.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>UK Calendar year</p></td><td><p>2000</p></td><td><p>2001</p></td><td><p>2002</p></td><td><p>2003</p></td><td><p>2004</p></td><td><p>2005</p></td><td><p>2006</p></td><td><p>2007</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>UK Spend (£millions)</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>7.8</p></td><td><p>7.7</p></td><td><p>17.3</p></td><td><p>28.9</p></td><td><p>19.6</p></td><td><p>8.9</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>UK Calendar year</p></td><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>UK Spend (£millions)</p></td><td><p>22.2</p></td><td><p>34.6</p></td><td><p>33.5</p></td><td><p>50.2</p></td><td><p>26.5</p></td><td><p>34.6</p></td><td><p>33.1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>2015 figures will be published later this year.</p><p>Details of the total Government of Bangladesh education budget can be found here: <a href="http://www.mof.gov.bd/en/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=68&amp;Itemid=1/" target="_blank">http://www.mof.gov.bd/en/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=68&amp;Itemid=1/</a>.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-05-11T16:26:36.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517861/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517861/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517861/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-05-05","Bangladesh: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much UK development aid to Bangladesh has been spent on education in each year since 2000; and what information her Department holds on the proportion the total Bangladesh education budget that UK development aid represents in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","36704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517862","Department for International Development","false","2016-05-11","<p>90% of contracts awarded during 2013-14, 86% of contracts awarded during 2014-15 and 94% of contracts awarded during 2015-16 were competitively tendered. During this time-frame there were a number of contracts which are not deemed as competitively tendered.</p><p>Any programmes not competitively tendered are subject to Procurement management review.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-05-11T16:30:08.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517862/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517862/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517862/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-05-05","Developing Countries: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of her Department's contracts for projects overseas were competitively tendered in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Edward Argar","Charnwood","Edward Argar","36649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517863","Department for International Development","false","2016-05-10","<p>The UK has supported significant improvements in primary school attendance through its contribution to the primary education sector programme and projects working with NGOs and civil society.</p><p>Overall primary school attendance increased in Bangladesh from 84% to 97% between 2010 and 2015.</p><p>Since 2010, DFID has supported 820,000 children (including 456, 000 girls) in primary education, of which 462,000 (261,000 girls) completed primary education.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-05-10T15:16:49.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517863/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517863/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517863/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-05-05","Bangladesh: Primary Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the effect of UK development aid on increasing primary school attendance in Bangladesh since 2000.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","36700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517864","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-05-11","<p>The level of pay for the judiciary is based on the recommendation of the independent Senior Salaries Review Body. Magistrates are volunteers and do not receive a salary.</p><p> </p><p>The judicial salaries and fee schedules can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/judicial-salaries-and-fees-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/judicial-salaries-and-fees-2016-to-2017</a></p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2016-05-11T10:54:23.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517864/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517864/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517864/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-05-05","Judiciary: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the average salary of (a) a district judge and (b) a magistrate was in the latest year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","36674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517865","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-05-10","<p>We will announce the conclusions of our review of fees in the Employment Tribunals in due course.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2016-05-10T16:06:35.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517865/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517865/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517865/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-05-05","Employment Tribunals Service: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he plans to publish his review of employment tribunal fees.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","36702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517866","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-05-10","<p>The information requested, could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-05-10T16:30:11.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517866/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517866/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517866/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-05-05","Reoffenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many (a) out-of-court restorative justice resolutions and (b) cautions were given to (i) people on suspended prison sentences and (ii) prisoners released on licence in the latest year for which information is held.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","36692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517867","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-05-11","<p>Where a magistrates’ court is dealing with a new offence which is triable either-way, and the defendant is an unrepresented serving prisoner who does not attend either in person or through a live link, the court will need to adjourn the case. This will enable either the defendant to attend, or the Crown Prosecution Service to consider alternative procedural routes.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2016-05-11T11:27:31.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517867/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517867/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517867/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-05-05","Criminal Proceedings: Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what options are available to a magistrates' court when an unrepresented serving prisoner refuses to leave their prison cell to face new either-way offence charges.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","36693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517868","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-05-11","<p>We keep maximum penalties under review. This includes sentencing trends, and whether the courts may be finding their sentencing powers inadequate.</p><p> </p><p>Data on the average sentence length for animal cruelty can be found in the Outcomes by offence table at the attached link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2014</a></p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2016-05-11T10:50:08.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517868/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517868/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517868/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-05-05","Animal Welfare: Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department plans to review the length of maximum sentence for animal cruelty offences.","false","Biography information for Alex Chalk","Cheltenham","Alex Chalk","36658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517869","Prime Minister","false","2016-05-10","<p>This year the Government is spending over £150 million more a year on pharmacies than in 2009/10. We are currently consulting on the introduction of a Pharmacy Access Scheme which will provide more NHS funds to many independent and rural pharmacies on the basis of factors such as location and the health needs of the local population. Details of the consultation on the ‘Community Pharmacy 2016/17 and beyond’ can be found on the GOV.UK website.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2016-05-10T16:38:15.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517869/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517869/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517869/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-05-05","Pharmacy: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, pursuant to his oral contribution of 20 April 2016, Official Report, column 915, in response to the Question from the hon. Member for Workington, and with reference to the letter to him of 21 April 2016 from that hon. Member and the oral contribution from that hon. Member of 25 April 2016, Official Report, column 1187, what scheme is in place to assist rural pharmacies; and what other support is provided by the Government to support independent pharmacies.","false","Biography information for Sue Hayman","Workington","Sue Hayman","36701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517870","Prime Minister","false","2016-05-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to the right hon. Member for Islington North (Mr Corbyn) on 4 May 2016, <em>Official Report</em>, column 163.</p><p>As set out in the Counter-Extremism Strategy, internationally we are building a more robust response to counter extremist ideology and propaganda, and continue to focus on strengthening international bodies and our partners. As Prime Minister I regularly have discussions on how we can promote British values of peace and tolerance and how to counter extremist ideology.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2016-05-10T16:20:56.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517870/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517870/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/517870/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-05-05","Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, with reference to the Government's Counter-Extremism Strategy, published in October 2015, whether in his official capacity he has shared a speaking platform with people who have expressed vocal or active opposition to the UK's fundamental values, including democracy, the rule of law, individual liberty and the mutual respect and tolerance of different faiths and beliefs, or who have called for the deaths of members of the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","36679"
